<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>6825</anchor> <rss>jms-0033.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-0033</addr>  <route>jms-0033.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>3</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Carrable map</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A morphism <tex>{ E } \xrightarrow {{ p }}{ B }</tex> in a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> is said to be <em>carrable</em> when for any <tex>{ A } \xrightarrow {{ f }}{ B }</tex>, the pullback <tex>{ E \times _{B}A } \xrightarrow {{ f^*p }}{ A }</tex> depicted below exists.</p>      <center><img src="resources/186864ce440db19b24f33465bf34b159-web.svg"/></center>  </mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>6826</anchor> <rss>jms-0031.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-0031</addr>  <route>jms-0031.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>3</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Exponentiable arrow</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="jms-0033.xml" type="local" title="Carrable map">carrable map</link> <tex>{ E } \xrightarrow {{ p }}{ B }</tex> in a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> is said to be <em>exponentiable</em> when it is <link href="jms-0032.xml" type="local" title="Exponentiable object">exponentiable</link> when viewed as an object of the slice category <tex>{ \mathcal {C} } _{ / B }</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>